  "commentary": "With SPX at 6812.33 sitting above the massive negative gamma cluster at 6800-6820 (-66.9B to -29.8B), dealers are currently forced to buy the rally as hedging flow, adding fuel to upward momentum in this breakout regime. The proximity to max positive gamma at 6840 (7.98B) creates a critical inflection point where dealer flow reverses from supportive buying to resistance selling. Watch 6800 as the key support level where amplified dealer buying kicks in on any pullback, while 6840 acts as the major resistance where dealers become natural sellers.\n\nBottom line: expect strong upward momentum until 6840, then heavy resistance.",
